list_definition_mean.definitions_word_en: a sailing ship in use (especially by Spain) from the 15th through 17th centuries, originally as a warship, later for trade. Galleons were mainly square-rigged and usually had three or more decks and masts.
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_en: a Spanish treasure galleon wrecked off the Florida Keys
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_vn: Một galleon kho báu Tây Ban Nha bị đắm từ các phím Florida
